          "tz": 120
        },
        "subject": "LU-6356 tgt: handle sec context requests properly",
        "message": "LU-6356 tgt: handle sec context requests properly\n\nIn case of requests of type SEC_CTX_INIT, SEC_CTX_INIT_CONT\nand SEC_CTX_FINI, no export is associated with the request\nyet, because these requests are sent before *_CONNECT requests.\nSo the normal *_common_slice handlers will not be called,\ngiven there is no reference to the target.\n\nSo add a special case for handling of SEC_CTX_INIT, SEC_CTX_INIT_CONT\nand SEC_CTX_FINI requests in tgt_handle_request0() and\ntgt_request_handle(), in order to directly send the reply.\n\nAlso fix error in sanityn.sh and see if it helps with Maloo.\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly testlist=sanityn\nSigned-off-by: Sebastien Buisson <sebastien.buisson@bull.net>\nChange-Id: I08cb42a8f0eaa45b5d3c5b8052d89ae749c14d61\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
